&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
    晴れた冬の日に&lt;a href=&quot;https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/京都御所&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;京都御所&lt;/a&gt;にある九條池と拾翠亭です。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Palaces" /><summary type="html">Kujo Pond and Shu Sui Tei Teahouse at the Kyoto Imperial Palace on a sunny winter day.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2021/2101_A7R01680-HDR.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Rokuoin Gate・鹿王院山門</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210108/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Rokuoin Gate・鹿王院山門" /><published>2021-01-08T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2021-01-08T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/rokuoin</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210108/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    The main gate of Rokuoin Temple in Arashiyama. It is famous for autumn leaves, but they are almost all gone now.
&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
   嵐山の鹿王院の山門。 紅葉で有名ですが、今ではほとんどなくなっています。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Temples" /><summary type="html">The main gate of Rokuoin Temple in Arashiyama. It is famous for autumn leaves, but they are almost all gone now.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2021/2101_IMG_2105.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Arashiyama Panorama ・嵐山のパノラマ</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210106/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Arashiyama Panorama ・嵐山のパノラマ" /><published>2021-01-06T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2021-01-06T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/arashiyama-pano</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210106/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    Looking across northern Kyoto from the Arashiyama Monkey Park on Mt. Arashi. The Katsura River is in the foreground; the Togetsu Bridge is covered by the trees at lower left. Mt Hiei is in the distance, center-right.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
     This is an 8-picture panorama shot on iPhone, stitched together in Adobe Lightroom.
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
   嵐山モンキーパークから京都北部を見渡す。 桂川が手前にあります。 比叡山は遠く、中央にあります。   
&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;これは、iPhoneで撮影した8枚のパノラマ写真で、Adobe Lightroomでつなぎ合わせたものです。&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Panoramas" /><category term="Views" /><summary type="html">Looking across northern Kyoto from the Arashiyama Monkey Park on Mt. Arashi. The Katsura River is in the foreground; the Togetsu Bridge is covered by the trees at lower left. Mt Hiei is in the distance, center-right. This is an 8-picture panorama shot on iPhone, stitched together in Adobe Lightroom.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2021/2101_IMG_2079-Pano-2.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Kiyomizu Temple・清水寺</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210104/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Kiyomizu Temple・清水寺" /><published>2021-01-04T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2021-01-04T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/kiyomizu</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210104/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
     The pagoda at Kiyomizudera, built in the 17th century.
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
   江戸時代初期に建てられた清水寺の塔。
    
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kiyomizudera" /><category term="Temples" /><summary type="html">The pagoda at Kiyomizudera, built in the 17th century.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2021/2101_IMG_2072.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Year of the Ox・丑年</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210102/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Year of the Ox・丑年" /><published>2021-01-02T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2021-01-02T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/ox</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210102/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
     An &lt;em&gt;Ema&lt;/em&gt; (wish tablet) with an Ox for the new year hangs at Yasaka Jinja.
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
   八坂神社に奉納された辛丑の絵馬。
    
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Shrines" /><summary type="html">An Ema (wish tablet) with an Ox for the new year hangs at Yasaka Jinja.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2021/2101_A7R01663.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Snow at Tenryu-ji・天龍寺の雪</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/201231/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Snow at Tenryu-ji・天龍寺の雪" /><published>2020-12-31T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2020-12-31T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/snow-at-tenryuji</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/201231/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
     Morning snow at Tenryu-ji Temple.
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
   天龍寺の朝雪。
    
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Gardens" /><category term="Tenryu-ji" /><category term="Temples" /><category term="Snow" /><summary type="html">Morning snow at Tenryu-ji Temple.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2020/2012_A7R01632.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Kikugetsu-tei・掬月亭</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/201229/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Kikugetsu-tei・掬月亭" /><published>2020-12-29T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2020-12-29T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/kikuretsutei</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/201229/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
     Kikugetsu-tei, or &lt;em&gt;Moon Scooping Pavilion&lt;/em&gt;, part of the large &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.my-kagawa.jp/static/en/ritsurin/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Ritsurin Garden&lt;/a&gt; in the city of Takamatsu. Dating from the early Edo period (early 17th century), this is one of the most beautiful gardens in Japan.
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
    高松の&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.my-kagawa.jp/ritsuringarden&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;栗林公園&lt;/a&gt;の菊月亭です。 江戸時代初期に建てられた、日本で最も美しい庭園のひとつです。
    
&lt;/p&gt; 

